{center}
{subhead}Elbox Releases Mediator PCI 1200 SX{def}
{left}
{pp}
{center}{image mediator_pci_1200_sx.iff}{pp}
{left}
{pp}
Elbox has released a new PCI expansion card for the A1200 called the Mediator PCI 1200 SX
which allows you to add standard PCI expansion cards to your Amiga. It requires an A1200
with 4MB Fast Ram.
{pp}
Features:
{pp}
* 6 PCI slots{p}
* Power Management Interface with wake up from LAN, USB etc {p}
* 66/33 MHz PCI Clock{p}
* 32 bit PCI data transters{p}
* 4 GB PCI memory space{p}
* Bus mastering and DMA on all slots {p}
* SDRAM/SGRAM of PCI graphics cards can be used as system memory{p}
* Address and data parity control support for sound cards{p}
* Interrupt controller with 4 lines
{pp}
For PCI card info and prices see Elbox web site{p}
http://www.elbox.com/
{pp}